      • loadEagerly

        public ApiComposer.Builder loadEagerly(boolean loadEagerly)
        Determine if the interface implementation will be lazy or eager.

        If set to true the ApiComposer created from this builder will initialize all interface method implementations immediately after the ApiComposer.compose(Class) is called.

        If set to false the ApiComposer.compose(Class) will only basic conditions for the supplied interface class and will actually resolve the interface method implementations on-demand (when the methods are called for the first time).

        Parameters:
        loadEagerly - the condition for whether the interface implementation should be lazy or eager
        Returns:
        A reference to the ApiComposer.Builder object
